    rationale: "This patient has the classic Blue Bloater phenotype of chronic bronchitis: cyanosis (from hypoxemia), edema (from cor pulmonale and right heart failure secondary to chronic hypoxia-driven pulmonary hypertension), and rhonchi (from excess mucus). The ABG shows hypoxemia, hypercapnia, and compensated respiratory acidosis \u2014 consistent with CO2 retention from mucus obstruction causing V/Q mismatch. The primary mechanism is V/Q mismatch from mucus plugging, not diffusion impairment. The Pink Puffer (emphysema) maintains oxygenation through increased work of breathing and does not typically present with cyanosis or edema until late disease.",
